name: Most common elements
description:
# Introduction

John was rushing to class, but he tripped and fell!

All of his neat folders have been mixed up, and he needs to sort them!

# Task

Given the current state of one of the folders, give the element(s) it most likely contained in any order. This process is called finding the ___mode___(s).

For example: Given the folder [1, 6, 3, 6], you should return [6]. 

Here are some more examples:
```
[6, 4, 3] -> [6, 4, 3]
[1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 5] -> [5]
[] -> []
[9, 9, 9] -> [9]
[1, 2, 1, 2] -> [1, 2]
```
